PyMol commands:

select a residue create a lolipop:

`
select res559, resi 559
show sticks, res559
color yellow, res559
`

hide the lolipop

`
hide sticks, resi 537
`

Use red white blue coloring:

`
spectrum b, red_white_blue, minimum=0, maximum=100
`


SIFT pipeline.
use script `mutant_notation.py` to create input for sift (requires txt input with one position per line)

I copied the fasta entry and (gapless) coordintes to 
https://sift.bii.a-star.edu.sg/sift-bin/SIFT_seq_submit2.pl


Then copies output from website into gene folder and ran `sift_table.py`.

--- Feb 28 ---

Add labels to CDY main cluster sequence:

# # Add codon site labels to specific residues
# label resi 393 and name CA, "Codon site: 331"
# label resi 537 and name CA, "Codon site: 475"
# label resi 559 and name CA, "Codon site: 497"


select res393, resi 393
show sticks, res393
color yellow, res393

select res537, resi 537
show sticks, res537
color yellow, res537

select res559, resi 559
show sticks, res559
color yellow, res559

label resi 393 and name CA, "331: Val -> Met"
label resi 537 and name CA, "475: Met -> Thr"
label resi 559 and name CA, "497: Arg -> His"

set label_size, 20
set label_color, yellow
set label_font_id, 7          # bold
set label_position, (2, 2, 10)

# play with position until the labels are readable

set label_position, (2, 2, 10)

Add labels to RBMY main cluster sequence:


Highlight positions
--
select res13, resi 13
show sticks, res13
color yellow, res13

select res71, resi 71
show sticks, res71
color yellow, res71

select res90, resi 90
show sticks, res90
color yellow, res90

label resi 13 and name CA, "13: Gly -> Ala"
label resi 71 and name CA, "72: Lys -> Thr"
label resi 90 and name CA, "92: Gly -> Asp"


